title: Diagrams as code
description: Diagrams as code's YAML JSON schema

name.description: A name of the diagram which is shown in the image

file_name.description: A file name of the image that would be created

format.description: A format of the image that would be created

direction.description: A direction of the diagram's resource

label_resources.description: Whether to label the diagram's resources

open.description: Whether to open the diagram's image after creating it

id.description: A unique identifier of the resource

of.description: Clusters and groups can have a list of resources inside them

to.description: A chain of identifiers to a resource via a dot from root

area.description: Indicates the preferred area for a node or empty cluster. For patchwork only

class.description: Classnames to attach to the node, edge, graph, or cluster's SVG element. For svg only

color.description: Basic drawing color for graphics, not text

colorscheme.description: A color scheme namespace: the context for interpreting color names

fillcolor.description: Color used to fill the background of a node or cluster

fixedsize.description: Whether to use the specified width and height attributes to choose node size (rather than sizing to fit the node contents)

fontsize.description: Font size, in points, used for text

gradientangle.description: If a gradient fill is being used, this determines the angle of the fill

group.description: Name for a group of nodes, for bundling edges avoiding crossings. For dot only

href.description: Synonym for URL. For map, postscript, svg only

id.description: Identifier for graph objects. For map, postscript, svg only

image.description: Gives the name of a file containing an image to be displayed inside a node

imagepos.description: Controls how an image is positioned within its containing node

imagescale.description: Controls how an image fills its containing node

labelloc.description: Vertical placement of labels for nodes, root graphs and clusters

layer.description: Specifies layers in which the node, edge or cluster is present

margin.description: For graphs, this sets x and y margins of canvas, in inches

nojustify.description: Whether to justify multiline text vs the previous text line (rather than the side of the container)

ordering.description: Constrains the left-to-right ordering of node edges. For dot only

orientation.description: node shape rotation angle, or graph orientation

penwidth.description: Specifies the width of the pen, in points, used to draw lines and curves

peripheries.description: Set number of peripheries used in polygonal shapes and cluster boundaries

pin.description: Keeps the node at the node's given input position. For neato, fdp only

pos.description: Position of node, or spline control points. For neato, fdp only

rects.description: Rectangles for fields of records, in points. For write only

regular.description: If true, force polygon to be regular

root.description: Specifies nodes to be used as the center of the layout. For twopi, circo only

samplepoints.description: Gives the number of points used for a circle/ellipse node

shape.description: Sets the shape of a node

shapefile.description: A file containing user-supplied node content

showboxes.description: Print guide boxes for debugging. For dot only

sortv.description: Sort order of graph components for ordering packmode packing

style.description: Set style information for components of the graph

target.description: If the object has a URL, this attribute determines which window of the browser is used for the URL. For map, svg only

tooltip.description: Tooltip (mouse hover text) attached to the node, edge, cluster, or graph. For cmap, svg only

URL.description: Hyperlinks incorporated into device-dependent output. For map, postscript, svg only

vertices.description: Sets the coordinates of the vertices of the node's polygon, in inches. For write only

xlabel.description: External label for a node or edge

xlp.description: Position of an exterior label, in points. For write only

z.description: Z-coordinate value for 3D layouts and displays

_background.description: A string in the xdot format specifying an arbitrary background

bb.description: Bounding box of drawing in points. For write only

beautify.description: Whether to draw leaf nodes uniformly in a circle around the root node in sfdp. For sfdp only

center.description: Whether to center the drawing in the output canvas

charset.description: Character encoding used when interpreting string input as a text label

class.description: Classnames to attach to the node, edge, graph, or cluster's SVG element. For svg only

clusterrank.description: Mode used for handling clusters. For dot only

colorscheme.description: A color scheme namespace: the context for interpreting color names

compound.description: If true, allow edges between clusters. For dot only

Damping.description: Factor damping force motions. For neato only

defaultdist.description: The distance between nodes in separate connected components. For neato only

dim.description: Set the number of dimensions used for the layout. For neato, fdp, sfdp only

dimen.description: Set the number of dimensions used for rendering. For neato, fdp, sfdp only

diredgeconstraints.description: Whether to constrain most edges to point downwards. For neato only

dpi.description: Specifies the expected number of pixels per inch on a display device. For bitmap output, svg only

esep.description: Margin used around polygons for purposes of spline edge routing. For neato only

fontnames.description: Allows user control of how basic fontnames are represented in SVG output. For svg only

fontpath.description: Directory list used by libgd to search for bitmap fonts

fontsize.description: Font size, in points, used for text

forcelabels.description: Whether to force placement of all xlabels, even if overlapping

gradientangle.description: If a gradient fill is being used, this determines the angle of the fill

href.description: Synonym for URL. For map, postscript, svg only

id.description: Identifier for graph objects. For map, postscript, svg only

imagepath.description: A list of directories in which to look for image files

inputscale.description: Scales the input positions to convert between length units. For neato, fdp only

K.description: Spring constant used in virtual physical model. For fdp, sfdp only

label_scheme.description: Whether to treat a node whose name has the form |edgelabel|* as a special node representing an edge label. For sfdp only

labelloc.description: Vertical placement of labels for nodes, root graphs and clusters

landscape.description: If true, the graph is rendered in landscape mode

layerlistsep.description: The separator characters used to split attributes of type layerRange into a list of ranges

layers.description: A linearly ordered list of layer names attached to the graph

layerselect.description: Selects a list of layers to be emitted

layersep.description: The separator characters for splitting the layers attribute into a list of layer names

levels.description: Number of levels allowed in the multilevel scheme. For sfdp only

levelsgap.description: strictness of neato level constraints. For neato only

lheight.description: Height of graph or cluster label, in inches. For write only

linelength.description: How long strings should get before overflowing to next line, for text output

lp.description: Label center position. For write only

lwidth.description: Width of graph or cluster label, in inches. For write only

margin.description: For graphs, this sets x and y margins of canvas, in inches

maxiter.description: Sets the number of iterations used. For neato, fdp only

mclimit.description: Scale factor for mincross (mc) edge crossing minimiser parameters. For dot only

mindist.description: Specifies the minimum separation between all nodes. For circo only

mode.description: Technique for optimizing the layout. For neato only

model.description: Specifies how the distance matrix is computed for the input graph. For neato only

newrank.description: Whether to use a single global ranking, ignoring clusters. For dot only

nodesep.description: In dot, nodesep specifies the minimum space between two adjacent nodes in the same rank, in inches

nojustify.description: Whether to justify multiline text vs the previous text line (rather than the side of the container)

normalize.description: normalizes coordinates of final layout. For neato, fdp, sfdp, twopi, circo only

notranslate.description: Whether to avoid translating layout to the origin point. For neato only

nslimit.description: Sets number of iterations in network simplex applications. For dot only

nslimit1.description: Sets number of iterations in network simplex applications. For dot only

oneblock.description: Whether to draw circo graphs around one circle. For circo only

ordering.description: Constrains the left-to-right ordering of node edges. For dot only

orientation.description: node shape rotation angle, or graph orientation

outputorder.description: Specify order in which nodes and edges are drawn

overlap.description: Determines if and how node overlaps should be removed. For fdp, neato only

overlap_scaling.description: Scale layout by factor, to reduce node overlap. For prism, neato, sfdp, fdp, circo, twopi only

overlap_shrink.description: Whether the overlap removal algorithm should perform a compression pass to reduce the size of the layout. For prism only

pack.description: Whether each connected component of the graph should be laid out separately, and then the graphs packed together

packmode.description: How connected components should be packed

pad.description: Inches to extend the drawing area around the minimal area needed to draw the graph

page.description: Width and height of output pages, in inches

pagedir.description: The order in which pages are emitted

quadtree.description: Quadtree scheme to use. For sfdp only

quantum.description: If quantum > 0.0, node label dimensions will be rounded to integral multiples of the quantum

rankdir.description: Sets direction of graph layout. For dot only

ranksep.description: Specifies separation between ranks. For dot, twopi only

ratio.description: Sets the aspect ratio (drawing height/drawing width) for the drawing

remincross.description: If there are multiple clusters, whether to run edge crossing minimization a second time. For dot only

repulsiveforce.description: The power of the repulsive force used in an extended Fruchterman-Reingold. For sfdp only

resolution.description: Synonym for dpi. For bitmap output, svg only

root.description: Specifies nodes to be used as the center of the layout. For twopi, circo only

rotate.description: If rotate=90, sets drawing orientation to landscape

rotation.description: Rotates the final layout counter-clockwise by the specified number of degrees. For sfdp only

scale.description: Scales layout by the given factor after the initial layout. For neato, twopi only

searchsize.description: During network simplex, the maximum number of edges with negative cut values to search when looking for an edge with minimum cut value. For dot only

sep.description: Margin to leave around nodes when removing node overlap. For fdp, neato only

showboxes.description: Print guide boxes for debugging. For dot only

size.description: Maximum width and height of drawing, in inches

smoothing.description: Specifies a post-processing step used to smooth out an uneven distribution of nodes. For sfdp only

sortv.description: Sort order of graph components for ordering packmode packing

splines.description: Controls how, and if, edges are represented

start.description: Parameter used to determine the initial layout of nodes. For neato, fdp, sfdp only

style.description: Set style information for components of the graph

stylesheet.description: A URL or pathname specifying an XML style sheet, used in SVG output. For svg only

target.description: If the object has a URL, this attribute determines which window of the browser is used for the URL. For map, svg only

TBbalance.description: Which rank to move floating (loose) nodes to. For dot only

tooltip.description: Tooltip (mouse hover text) attached to the node, edge, cluster, or graph. For cmap, svg only

truecolor.description: Whether internal bitmap rendering relies on a truecolor color model or uses. For bitmap output only

URL.description: Hyperlinks incorporated into device-dependent output. For map, postscript, svg only

voro_margin.description: Tuning margin of Voronoi technique. For neato, fdp, sfdp, twopi, circo only

xdotversion.description: Determines the version of xdot used in output. For xdot only

arrowhead.description: Style of arrowhead on the head node of an edge

arrowtail.description: Style of arrowhead on the tail node of an edge

class.description: Classnames to attach to the node, edge, graph, or cluster's SVG element. For svg only

color.description: Basic drawing color for graphics, not text

colorscheme.description: A color scheme namespace: the context for interpreting color names

constraint.description: If false, the edge is not used in ranking the nodes. For dot only

decorate.description: Whether to connect the edge label to the edge with a line

edgehref.description: Synonym for edgeURL. For map, svg only

edgetarget.description: Browser window to use for the edgeURL link. For map, svg only

edgetooltip.description: Tooltip annotation attached to the non-label part of an edge. For cmap, svg only

edgeURL.description: The link for the non-label parts of an edge. For map, svg only

fillcolor.description: Color used to fill the background of a node or cluster

fontsize.description: Font size, in points, used for text

head_lp.description: Center position of an edge's head label. For write only

headclip.description: If true, the head of an edge is clipped to the boundary of the head node

headhref.description: Synonym for headURL. For map, svg only

headlabel.description: Text label to be placed near head of edge

headport.description: Indicates where on the head node to attach the head of the edge

headtarget.description: Browser window to use for the headURL link. For map, svg only

headtooltip.description: Tooltip annotation attached to the head of an edge. For cmap, svg only

headURL.description: If defined, headURL is output as part of the head label of the edge. For map, svg only

href.description: Synonym for URL. For map, postscript, svg only

id.description: Identifier for graph objects. For map, postscript, svg only

labelangle.description: The angle (in degrees) in polar coordinates of the head & tail edge labels

labeldistance.description: Scaling factor for the distance of headlabel / taillabel from the head / tail nodes

labelfloat.description: If true, allows edge labels to be less constrained in position

labelfontcolor.description: Color used for headlabel and taillabel

labelfontsize.description: Font size of headlabel and taillabel

labelhref.description: Synonym for labelURL. For map, svg only

labeltarget.description: Browser window to open labelURL links in. For map, svg only

labeltooltip.description: Tooltip annotation attached to label of an edge. For cmap, svg only

labelURL.description: If defined, labelURL is the link used for the label of an edge. For map, svg only

layer.description: Specifies layers in which the node, edge or cluster is present

len.description: Preferred edge length, in inches. For neato, fdp only

lhead.description: Logical head of an edge. For dot only

lp.description: Label center position. For write only

ltail.description: Logical tail of an edge. For dot only

minlen.description: Minimum edge length (rank difference between head and tail). For dot only

nojustify.description: Whether to justify multiline text vs the previous text line (rather than the side of the container)

penwidth.description: Specifies the width of the pen, in points, used to draw lines and curves

pos.description: Position of node, or spline control points. For neato, fdp only

samehead.description: Edges with the same head and the same samehead value are aimed at the same point on the head. For dot only

sametail.description: Edges with the same tail and the same sametail value are aimed at the same point on the tail. For dot only

showboxes.description: Print guide boxes for debugging. For dot only

style.description: Set style information for components of the graph

tail_lp.description: Position of an edge's tail label, in points. For write only

tailclip.description: If true, the tail of an edge is clipped to the boundary of the tail node

tailhref.description: Synonym for tailURL. For map, svg only

taillabel.description: Text label to be placed near tail of edge

tailport.description: Indicates where on the tail node to attach the tail of the edge

tailtarget.description: Browser window to use for the tailURL link. For map, svg only

tailtooltip.description: Tooltip annotation attached to the tail of an edge. For cmap, svg only

tailURL.description: If defined, tailURL is output as part of the tail label of the edge. For map, svg only

target.description: If the object has a URL, this attribute determines which window of the browser is used for the URL. For map, svg only

tooltip.description: Tooltip (mouse hover text) attached to the node, edge, cluster, or graph. For cmap, svg only

URL.description: Hyperlinks incorporated into device-dependent output. For map, postscript, svg only

xlabel.description: External label for a node or edge

xlp.description: Position of an exterior label, in points. For write only
